cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.OS, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the costs and trade-offs of providing transactional consistent reads in a distributed storage system, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC), databases (cs.DB), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the impact of read consistency on system performance, which is relevant to operating systems (cs.OS) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
